  <description type="morphology">Stems 30–50(–80) cm, mostly simple, sparsely tomentose. Leaves ± white; blades broadly obovate to oblong, 4–10 × 1.5–4 cm, relatively deeply lobed (lobes, lanceolate, 1/3+ blade lengths, acute), faces tomentose (usually less densely adaxially). Heads in racemiform arrays 4–7 × 2–4 cm. Involucres (broadly campanulate), 4–5 × 4–8 mm. Florets: pistillate 8–10; bisexual 20–30; corollas 1.5–2 mm.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering mid–late summer.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Mountains, usually in loamy soils;</description>
  <description type="elevation">1800–3000 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Alta., B.C.; Calif., Idaho, Mont., Nev., Oreg., Utah, Wash., Wyo.</description>
  <number>37c.</number>
  <discussion>Subspecies candicans is broadly circumscribed in this treatment. Variants within the complex, especially var. latiloba, may merit segregation.</discussion>
